history.text: Hello!
Have you seen Dunkirk?
No I haven't.
What type of movie is it?
The movie came out this past year and was directed by Christopher Nolan. Its a historical drama. The cast & the story line is breathtaking.
That sounds very interesting. What event in history is it portraying?
It is about the World War II's evacuation of Dunkirk.
Sounds like an interesting topic. Probably something I'd go out and see.
Have you seen the film personally already?

Nolan does a great job directing this film, and has a great vision. What I think makes this movie unique is that has 3 main situations happening and they are all happening simultaneously and different time increments.
I have seen it personally, one of my favorite movies of all time.
I haven't seen many films in the past few months (a bit behind). Sounds like it is very captivating.
Do you know much about the background and World War II
It's been a while since I've brushed up on the finer details, but yes I do have a good idea about WWII.
What else about the movie did you like?

The main portion of the movie revolves around a single soldier that was the sole survivor of his team that was attacked. It follows him as he tries to get on a huge evacuation ship. You follow him and the relationships he make with other soldiers.
How did you like the actor who portrayed that role?

That role was portrayed by Fionn Whitehead, I have never seen this actor in any other roles so he was new to me. I believe he did a really good job. He wasn't my favorite seems very novice. especially with all the other experienced actors
I've never heard of him either. Maybe it's his first big film.
Are you familiar with other works by Christopher Nolan?
His movies also seem to be paired with great soundtracks as well.
Yes, I like a handful of his movies. In a lot of his films he uses Tom Hardy. I am a huge Tom Hardy Fan.
Very true! I too am a fan of Hardy.
He plays a spitfire Pilot in Dunkirk, he does an amazing job in this role.
That sounds like a great fitting role for him.
It was, he didn't have a large role, but what parts he was in were really good
Me personally I prefer when a movie has a realistic end rather than an "Happy Ending"
I'd say it depends on my "mood of the day." But for a good drama film, a realistic ending is definitely preferred.
Did Dunkirk have a "happy ending"?

I feel like Dunkirk had an amazing realistic ending. So the main character did get to evacuate but, after losing some of the friends he gained along the way. Tom Hardy's character was captured. There were also some deaths of some key characters.
It over all had a happy ending, but a very realistic one.
That's good. Makes it a bit less predictable too at the end.
Would you say this is your most favorite Christopher Nolan film?
I think so too. Really good movie, you should watch it sometime, if I haven't spoiled to much for you.
I think so, but Inception is a close second.
I think I definitely will! I was a huge fan of Inception--saw it 3-4 times in theaters.
It was nice chatting with you. Hope you have a great day!
You too!!

User was very responsive & easy to talk to. 
Good Conversation.

uid2response.feedback: The movie sounds very engaging with a unique way of telling the historical drama of Dunkirk.
